reason.tex:
%text
\[ \lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{\sin x}{x} = 1.\] This is a standard result.

However, \[ \lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{\sin Mx}{Nx} = \dfrac{M}{N}.\] The proof
is as given below 

%
\begin{align}
\lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{\sin Mx}{Nx} &= \lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{\dfrac{\sin Mx}{Mx}}{\dfrac{Nx}{Mx}}
= \dfrac{M}{N}\cdot\lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{\sin Mx}{Mx}\\
\text{Now, if } z &= Mx\text{ then as }x\to 0,z\to 0\\
\therefore \lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{\sin Mx}{Mx} &= \lim_{z\to 0}\dfrac{\sin z}{z} = 1 \\
\therefore \lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{\sin Mx}{Nx} &= \dfrac{M}{N}\cdot\lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{\sin Mx}{Mx} = \dfrac{M}{N}
\end{align}
